.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1687117","id":1687117,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2ODcxMTc=","updated_at":"2011-07-30T06:01:13.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1687117","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/314997?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zz85","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDk5Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"zz85","type":"User","id":314997,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"btw really nice work with the shadow maps! :) wonder if it works with particle...\n","created_at":"2011-07-30T20:16:06.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1690750","id":1690750,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2OTA3NTA=","updated_at":"2011-07-30T20:16:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1690750","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/314997?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zz85","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDk5Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"zz85","type":"User","id":314997,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@mrdoob, its seems to remove a particle from a group, the visibility must be disabled first in addition to using group.removeChild(particle); for canvas renderer?\n\nWhen I check the length of children it seems like its have already been removed so I use particle.visible = false; to hide it to prevent glitches. Not sure if this is the correct way of doing it. \n\nSee http:\/\/jsdo.it\/zz85\/27tB line 128.\n\nalso I'm not sure if my experimental particle engine should be used inside three.js so I'm twinkling with my experiments @ https:\/\/github.com\/zz85\/sparks.js\n","created_at":"2011-07-31T19:55:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1696297","id":1696297,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2OTYyOTc=","updated_at":"2011-07-31T19:55:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1696297","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/314997?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zz85","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDk5Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"zz85","type":"User","id":314997,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Nice to see them live ;)\n\nDidn't get yet to try shadow maps with `ParticleSystem`, but in theory at least something should work - shadow casting for static ones using depth buffer. Shadow receiving should work after some shader tweaks. Most messy part would be shader-based animation, will probably need to add some hooks to WebGLRenderer for custom depth materials.\n","created_at":"2011-07-31T20:17:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1696376","id":1696376,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE2OTYzNzY=","updated_at":"2011-07-31T20:17:07.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1696376","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/438022?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/alteredq","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzODAyMg==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"alteredq","type":"User","id":438022,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@alteredq Using the new attribute support, managed to integrate my particle demo with Webgl particle's system. :)\n\n<img src=\"http:\/\/i51.tinypic.com\/20ush34.png\"\/>\n\nSee http:\/\/jabtunes.com\/labs\/particles\/example3.html (in this example, particle systems batch create 1000 particles, of which only around 500 are used. the concept of pool came in useful again for reusing particle systems'  particles)\n\nNot sure if its a feature or something, I realized that group.sortParticles (where group is ParticleSystem) has to be set to true, otherwise, size and color changes does not update after particleSystems get created.\n\nAlso, is there a way to load an texture from a generated canvas rather than from a server? \n","created_at":"2011-08-03T05:22:33.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1715590","id":1715590,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE3MTU1OTA=","updated_at":"2018-11-19T14:24:13.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1715590","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/314997?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zz85","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDk5Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"zz85","type":"User","id":314997,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Nice ;)\n\n> Not sure if its a feature or something, I realized that group.sortParticles (where group is ParticleSystem) has to be set to true, otherwise, size and color changes does not update after particleSystems get created.\n\n`ParticleSystems` are like other objects: by default they are assumed to be static. \n\nIf you want to do dynamic updates of standard attributes in runtime, you need to set `geometry.__dirtyXXX` flags to ask for buffer update. \n\nSo for vertices, it's `geometry.__dirtyVertices = true;` and for colors it's `geometry.__dirtyColors = true;` after you change something. \n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/dev\/examples\/webgl_particles_dynamic.html#L589\n\nCustom attributes have `needsUpdate` flags:\n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/dev\/examples\/webgl_custom_attributes_particles.html#L213\n\n(meshes additionally also need to have set `mesh.dynamic = true` to preserve their internal typed array buffers)\n\nNow with sorting, particles get buffer updates by default, because sorting have to update buffers in any case. \n\nBut if you don't need sorting, it's better not to have it enabled, it's a major performance drain.\n\n> Also, is there a way to load an texture from a generated canvas rather than from a server?\n\nYes, you can pass in 2d canvas element as parameter to `Texture` instead of image:\n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/dev\/examples\/webgl_objconvert_test.html#L91\n\nAnd since yesterday there is also `DataTexture` if you want to create textures directly from raw bytes in Typed Array.\n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/commit\/01bebe5c40cb5177f0c7c02b13c4581d24001f05\n","created_at":"2011-08-03T15:20:27.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1718831","id":1718831,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE3MTg4MzE=","updated_at":"2011-08-03T15:20:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1718831","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/438022?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/alteredq","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzODAyMg==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"alteredq","type":"User","id":438022,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"thank you for the detailed explanation. avoiding sortParticles and using __dirtyColors I managed to add 100,000 particle systems vertices rendering ~5,000 particles on screen. \n\nit took me a while to get that canvas texture working - basically i was doing \n\n``` javascript\nuniforms = {\n        texture:   { type: \"t\", value: 0, texture: new THREE.Texture(canvas)}               \n};\n```\n\ninstead of \n\n``` javascript\nvar aTexture = new THREE.Texture(canvas);\naTexture.needsUpdate = true;\nuniforms = {\n        texture:   { type: \"t\", value: 0, texture:aTexture }                \n};\n```\n\nAlso I tried doing \n\n``` javascript\nvar idata = context.getImageData(0,0,canvas.width, canvas.height);\nvar aTexture= THREE.DataTexture (new Uint8Array(idata), canvas.width, canvas.height);\naTexture.needsUpdate = true;\n```\n\nwhich doesn't seems to work. ideally, shouldn't imagedata work with THREE.Texture? The tests results seems to show that imagedata performances quite good.\n\nhttp:\/\/jsperf.com\/texture-sources\n\nAlso, do you think I should add my particles examples to three.js too?\n","created_at":"2011-08-04T04:34:34.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1724418","id":1724418,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE3MjQ0MTg=","updated_at":"2011-08-04T07:18:51.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1724418","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/314997?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zz85","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDk5Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"zz85","type":"User","id":314997,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/zz85\/orgs"}},{"index":11,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Oh yes, textures need to have `needsUpdate` flag set. \n\nFor image ones this is done inside `ImageUtils.loadTexture`, for anything user created it needs to be done explicitly.\n\n> which doesn't seems to work. ideally, shouldn't imagedata work with THREE.Texture? The tests results seems to show that imagedata performances quite good.\n\nHmmm, interesting that there are such big performance differences.\n\n`ImageData` should work just with plain `Texture` - never tried it, but in WebGL specs it has the same `texImage2D` signature as image \/ canvas \/ video textures (which means it doesn't need explicit width and height):\n\nYou can try this:\n\n``` javascript\nvar idata = context.getImageData( 0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height );\nvar aTexture = THREE.Texture ( idata );\naTexture.needsUpdate = true;\n```\n\n> Also, do you think I should add my particles examples to three.js too?\n\nYes, that would be nice ;)\n","created_at":"2011-08-04T10:23:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375#issuecomment-1725889","id":1725889,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/375","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE3MjU4ODk=","updated_at":"2011-08-04T10:23:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/1725889","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/438022?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/alteredq","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alteredq\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VX